body:
New error: 
*RuntimeError: [ONNXRuntimeError] : 1 : GENERAL ERROR : Exception during initialization: /onnxruntime_src/onnxruntime/core/framework/node_index_info.cc:82 onnxruntime::NodeIndexInfo::Init(const TValidNodes&, onnxruntime::NodeIndex, const onnxruntime::MLValueNameIdxMap&)::<lambda(const onnxruntime::NodeArg&, bool)> [with TValidNodes = onnxruntime::ValidNodes<const std::vector<const onnxruntime::Node*> >] status.IsOK() was false. Could not find MLValue with name 'const_1'*

This should be related with two issues:
1. One should be known issue in https://github.com/Microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/master/onnxruntime/core/optimizer/optimizer_execution_frame.cc#L53. It does not support control flow ops by design, @weixingzhang 
2. One may be a bug in constant folding https://github.com/Microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/master/onnxruntime/core/optimizer/constant_folding.cc#L26. I believe that for constant folding it should use OpKernelContextInternal. @weixingzhang  @kkaranasos

Constant folding uses OpKernelContext (and not OpKernelContextInternal) on purpose, so that we don't rely on the InferenceSession in the optimizer.
For now we disabled constant folding for subgraphs (https://github.com/Microsoft/onnxruntime/pull/858) until we provide a proper support for it.
I ran the test code with the latest onnxruntime code and it was successful. @lucienwang1009 can you please check to see if it works for you?
Closing as I can't reproduce. Please re-open if this is still an issue.
